ce:section.ce:para:
The fabricated optosensor was used to determine florfenicol in milk. Low concentrations of florfenicol were found (

                        Table 1
                        ). The accuracy of the method was then assessed in terms of recovery, which was carried out by spiking milk with standard florfenicol at 1.0, 10.0, 50.0 and 100.0 µg L-1. Recoveries were in the range of 90.47–101.46 % and the RSDs were below 3 %. The inter-day (n = 3) and intra-day (n = 6) repeatability of the developed method were also evaluated in samples spiked at 10.0 μg L-1. Inter-day and intra-day RSDs were 3.2 % and 2.0 %, respectively. These results demonstrated that the developed optosensor was a reliable method of determining florfenicol.
